/-!
# Gamma-Deviation Synthesis

This file bridges the algebraic product-difference decomposition
(`MobiusSynthesis.lean`) with the combinatorial `M_Œ≥(H)` tuple-counting bounds
(`Combinatorics.lean`, `GammaRangeSum.lean`).

## Overview

In the Granville‚ÄìKurlberg proof (¬ß3.1), the sum over lattice points `h`
of the deviation product `‚àè_{p ‚àà T} |N_p(h) ‚àí Œº_p|` is reorganised by
fibering over the *gamma value* `Œ≥` of each tuple. The gamma value is
defined via `gammaProdOfBoxPoint`: for `c = ‚àè_{p ‚àà T} p` and a lattice
point `h` in the scaled box, the gamma product
`Œ≥(h) = ‚àè_j lcm_{i<j} gcd(c, |h'_j ‚àí h'_i|)` (where `h' = (0, h)`)
encodes the collision structure.

The summation rearrangement uses `Finset.sum_fiberwise_of_maps_to` to
partition the box lattice points by their gamma value, then bounds the
per-fiber deviation product and counts the fiber cardinality using
`countTuplesWithGammaProd`.

## Main Results

* `deviation_prod_le_perGammaWeight` ‚Äî Pointwise bound: for each box point `h`,
  `|‚àè_{p ‚àà T} (N_p ‚àí Œº_p)| ‚â§ perGammaDeviationWeight Œµ k Œ© T Œ≥(h)`.
* `fiber_card_le_countTuplesWithGammaProd` ‚Äî Fiber cardinality: the number of
  box points with gamma value `Œ≥` is at most `countTuplesWithGammaProd (k‚àí1) Œ≥ H`.
* `deviation_sum_le_gamma_sum` ‚Äî Synthesis: the total deviation sum is bounded
  by `‚àë_Œ≥ w(Œ≥) ¬∑ M_Œ≥(H)`.

## References

* [A. Granville, P. Kurlberg, *Poisson statistics via the Chinese remainder theorem*]
  [arXiv:math/0412135v2], ¬ß3.1
-/

