/--
**Pointwise Weight Bound.** For a single lattice point `h` in the box,
the absolute deviation product `|‚àè_{p ‚àà T} (localCount ‚àí localMean)|` is
bounded by `perGammaDeviationWeight Œµ k Œ© T Œ≥`, where `Œ≥` is the gamma
product `gammaProdOfBoxPoint T h`.

The proof splits `T` into collision primes (`p ‚à£ radical Œ≥`) and
well-distributed primes (`p ‚à§ radical Œ≥`):
- Collision primes get the trivial bound `|localCount ‚àí localMean| ‚â§ p`
  via `abs_localCount_sub_localMean_le_p`.
- Well-distributed primes: since `p ‚à§ radical Œ≥` and `p ‚à£ ‚àè T`, the
  tuple `Fin.cons 0 h` is injective mod `p`, so the `WellDistributed`
  hypothesis gives `|localCount ‚àí localMean| ‚â§ (1‚àí|Œ©|/p)¬∑p^{‚àíŒµ}¬∑Œº_p`.

